metadata.title: Abundance and Taxa Composition of Copepod Nauplii over Southeastern Bering Sea Deep Water Spawning Grounds of Walleye Pollock (Theragra Chalcogramma)

creators.name: University of Alaska Fairbanks (UAF), School of Fisheries
Ocean Sciences (SFOS), Institute of Marine Science (IMS)

metadata.description: To describe the nauplii taxa and recruitment in Aleutian basin, this project examined the abundance, taxa, stage and size of copepod nauplii available as prey for walleye pollock larvae in their deep water spawning grounds of the southeastern Bering Sea.
metadata.notes:
Purpose: To describe the nauplii taxa and recruitment in Aleutian basin, this project examined the abundance, taxa, stage and size of copepod nauplii available as prey for walleye pollock larvae in their deep water spawning grounds of the southeastern Bering Sea.
